import pandas as pd # Data processing, CSV file I/O (e.g. pd.read_csv)
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split # a method used to split data into train and test sets
from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier # Algorithm that uses a set of rules to make decisions
#from sklearn import metrics
from sklearn import tree # a non-parametric supervised learning method used for classification and regression
from sklearn.metrics import f1_score, accuracy_score, confusion_matrix, classification_report
import graphviz # a module used to create graph objects
import pydotplus # a Python Interface to Graphviz's Dot language
from IPython.display import Image # a class to load and display a local image in the IPython notebook
from sklearn.tree import export_graphviz # to export a decision tree in DOT format

In [10]:
# Split data into train and test sets,  the percentage of the data that should be held over for testing is 20%
x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(x, y, test_size = 0.2)
In [11]:
classifier = DecisionTreeClassifier(max_depth=5, criterion='entropy') # Create an instance of DecisionTreeClassifier
model = classifier.fit(x_train,y_train) # Train the algorithm on the training data
In [12]:
features = ("having_IP_Address", "URL_Length", "Shortining_Service", "having_At_Symbol", "double_slash_redirecting",
            "Prefix_Suffix", "having_Sub_Domain", "SSLfinal_State", "Domain_registeration_length", "Favicon", "port",
            "HTTPS_token", "Request_URL", "URL_of_Anchor", "Links_in_tags", "SFH", "Submitting_to_email", "Abnormal_URL",
            "Redirect", "on_mouseover", "RightClick", "popUpWindow", "Iframe", "age_of_domain", "DNSRecord", "web_traffic",
            "Page_Rank", "Google_Index", "Links_pointing_to_page", "Statistical_report"
)
name = ('1', '-1')

# Export a decision tree in DOT format
dot_data = tree.export_graphviz(model, out_file=None, 
                      feature_names = features, class_names =  name,
                      filled=True, rounded=True, 
                      special_characters=True)  

# Print the decision tree as an image
graph = pydotplus.graph_from_dot_data(dot_data)
Image(graph.create_png())
